<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-4128] stress tool hangs forever on timeout or error</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-4128</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The stress tool hangs forever if it encounters a timeout or exception. CTRL-C will kill it if run from a terminal, but when running it from a script (like a dtest) it hangs the script forever. It would be great for scripting it if a reasonable error code was returned when things go wrong.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;To duplicate, clear out /var/lib/cassandra and then run &quot;stress --operation=READ&quot;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;This happens in every version of the stress tool, that I know of, including calling it from the dtests.&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
